('Garage UK', 'A genre of electronic music originating from England in the early 1990s.'),
('Chillout', 'A loosely defined umbrella term for styles of electronic music characterized by their mellow style and mid-tempo beats.'),
('Downtempo', 'A genre of electronic music similar to ambient music but usually with a beat or groove.'),
('Industrial', 'A genre of music that draws on harsh, transgressive or provocative sounds and themes.'),
('Glitch', 'A genre of electronic music that emerged in the late 1990s. It has been described as an "aesthetic of failure".'),
('Breakbeat', 'A broad style of electronic or dance-oriented music which utilizes breaks, often sampled from earlier recordings in funk, jazz, and R&B.'),

