('Minimalism', 'A form of art music or other compositional practice that employs limited or minimal musical materials.'),
('Neoclassical', 'A twentieth-century trend, particularly current in the interwar period, in which composers sought to return to aesthetic precepts associated with the broadly defined concept of "classicism".'),
('Avant-Garde', 'Music that is considered to be at the forefront of experimentation or innovation in its field.'),

